President Donald Trump has announced his intent to nominate Jeffrey A. Rosen to the position of Deputy Attorney General at the Department of Justice. Rosen currently serves as Deputy Secretary of the U.S. Department of Transportation and has a background in law, having been a senior partner at Kirkland & Ellis LLP. He has also held positions at the White House Office of Management and Budget and the U.S. Department of Transportation. Rosen has a B.A. in economics from Northwestern University and a J.D. from Harvard Law School.